{%- comment -%}
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  AT Menu Data — JIT-fetchable section for the heavy AT menu content
  ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  Purpose
  -------
  The AT menu's heavy content (the ~100-brand grid + every category
  subnav, both mobile drawer views and desktop mega-panel content) used
  to render alongside the header section on every page load — gated only
  by Horizon's `eager_loading` (`section.index == blank`) trick to defer
  to a Section Rendering API re-fetch of the WHOLE header. That still
  caused two problems on cold-cache pages:

    1. The header section's render time on origin includes the AT menu
       block work even on the first (skeleton) render.
    2. The SRA re-fetch's `render;dur` is dominated by ~100 brand
       metaobject lookups + per-segment cart/customer state, so cache
       hit rate is poor for the typical visitor segment.

  This section moves the heavy content out into its own dedicated
  section that:

    - Is NOT rendered anywhere in any layout or section group, so it
      adds zero overhead to initial page renders and is invisible to
      crawlers walking the HTML graph.
    - Is fetched explicitly via the Section Rendering API
      (`/?section_id=at-menu-data`, triggered by JS on real user
      intent — hamburger pointerdown on mobile, nav hover on desktop)
      and assets/at-menu.js distributes the views into the live
      <at-menu-panel> (mobile) and <at-brands-panel> (desktop) custom
      element instances rendered by the AT Menu block.
    - Is segment-agnostic (no cart/customer/currency dependency in the
      output), so origin page_cache + Cloudflare caches it efficiently
      across all visitor segments.

  Routing markers
  ---------------
  Each emitted view carries a data attribute so the JS adopter knows
  where to put it:

    [data-at-mount="mobile-view"]            mobile drawer view
                                             (data-view selects which)
    [data-at-mount="desktop-cat-content"]    desktop cat-content body
                                             (data-cat selects which)

  Configuration
  -------------
  Static sections file-mounted via the SRA endpoint do not appear in
  Horizon's customizer (no place to render them = no editable instance).
  Settings here therefore always resolve to schema defaults; the two
  link_list handles (which can't have schema defaults) are hardcoded
  below to match the AT Menu block in sections/header-group.json.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  # ─── Configuration ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  # Static sections rendered from layout/theme.liquid are not editable in
  # Horizon's customizer, so this section's schema settings can never be
  # changed from defaults. We therefore source values from section.settings
  # (which falls back to schema defaults) but hardcode the two link_list
  # handles below — link_list schema types don't accept defaults.
  #
  # IMPORTANT: keep these in sync with the AT Menu block configuration in
  # sections/header-group.json (block type "_at-menu", id "at-menu").
  assign s = section.settings
  assign cats_handle    = 'at-categories'
  assign brands_handle  = 'at-brands'
  assign brands_item    = s.at_brands_item_handle | default: 'brands'
  assign icon_source    = s.at_brand_icon_source  | default: 'auto'
  assign show_search    = s.at_show_brand_search
  assign cols           = s.at_brands_panel_columns  | default: 4
  assign mobile_cols    = s.at_brands_mobile_columns | default: 2
  assign img_radius     = s.at_brand_image_border_radius | default: 4

  assign cats_ll   = linklists[cats_handle]
  assign brands_ll = linklists[brands_handle]

  # Resolve the brands sidebar item from the categories linklist
  assign brands_cat_link = nil
  if cats_ll != blank
    for cat_link in cats_ll.links
      if cat_link.handle == brands_item
        assign brands_cat_link = cat_link
        break
      endif
    endfor
  endif

  # Brand source: prefer dedicated brands linklist, fall back to category sub-links
  assign brand_source_links = blank
  if brands_ll != blank
    assign brand_source_links = brands_ll.links
  elsif brands_cat_link != blank
    assign brand_source_links = brands_cat_link.links
  endif

  assign brand_total = 0
  if brand_source_links != blank
    assign brand_total = brand_source_links.size
  endif

  assign brand_grid_rows = 1
  if brand_total > 0
    assign brand_grid_rows = brand_total | plus: cols | minus: 1 | divided_by: cols
  endif

  # AT: Mobile uses an alphabetical letter-grouped grid; desktop preserves
  # the merchant-defined linklist order. Sort once into `sorted_brands` so
  # the mobile loop can emit letter headers via a single-pass state machine
  # (`assign last_letter`), rather than the previous O(letters × brands)
  # nested loop that was the dominant complexity contributor on cold-cache
  # mobile fetches of this section (the cause of the 5xx that produced
  # "There was a problem loading this website" when the hamburger opened).
  assign sorted_brands = brand_source_links
  if brand_source_links != blank
    assign sorted_brands = brand_source_links | sort: 'title'
  endif

  # Build alphabet array from sorted brand links (mobile A-Z quick-jump bar)
  assign all_letters = ''
  if sorted_brands != blank
    for brand_link in sorted_brands
      assign letter = brand_link.title | upcase | slice: 0, 1
      unless all_letters contains letter
        assign all_letters = all_letters | append: letter | append: ','
      endunless
    endfor
  endif
  assign alpha_letters = all_letters | split: ','
-%}

{%- if cats_ll != blank -%}
  <at-menu-data hidden>

    {%- comment -%} ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      MOBILE DRAWER VIEWS
      Each emits as a [data-at-mount="mobile-view"] container holding a
      single `.at-panel__view` element. assets/at-menu.js moves the
      contained view into the live <at-menu-panel> as a sibling of the
      main view.
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ {%- endcomment -%}

    {%- if brand_source_links != blank -%}
      <div data-at-mount="mobile-view">
        <div class="at-panel__view at-panel__view--brands" data-view="brands" hidden>

          <div class="at-panel__header">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="at-panel__back"
              aria-label="{{ 'actions.back' | t | default: 'Back' }}"
              on:click="/back"
            >
              <span class="svg-wrapper">{{- 'icon-chevron-left.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}</span>
            </button>
            <h2 class="at-panel__title">{{- brands_cat_link.title | default: 'Brands' | escape -}}</h2>
            <button
              type="button"
              class="at-panel__close"
              aria-label="{{ 'actions.close' | t | default: 'Close menu' }}"
              on:click="header-drawer/close"
            >
              <span class="svg-wrapper">{{- 'icon-close.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}</span>
            </button>
          </div>

          {%- if show_search -%}
            <div class="at-panel__search-wrapper" role="search">
              <span class="at-panel__search-icon svg-wrapper" aria-hidden="true">
                {{- 'icon-search.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}
              </span>
              <label for="at-panel-brand-search" class="visually-hidden">
                {{ 'content.search' | t | default: 'Search brands' }}
              </label>
              <input
                ref="searchInput"
                id="at-panel-brand-search"
                type="search"
                class="at-panel__search"
                placeholder="{{ 'placeholders.search' | t | default: 'Search brands…' }}"
                autocomplete="off"
                aria-controls="at-panel-brands-body"
                aria-label="{{ 'content.search' | t | default: 'Search brands' }}"
              >
              <button
                ref="searchClear"
                type="button"
                class="at-panel__search-clear"
                aria-label="{{ 'actions.clear' | t | default: 'Clear' }}"
                hidden
              >
                <span class="svg-wrapper">{{- 'icon-close.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}</span>
              </button>
            </div>
          {%- endif -%}

          <span
            ref="brandCount"
            class="at-panel__brand-count"
            aria-live="polite"
            aria-atomic="true"
          >
            {{- brand_total -}}
          </span>

          <div
            class="at-panel__body"
            id="at-panel-brands-body"
            ref="brandsBody"
            role="list"
            aria-label="{{ brands_cat_link.title | default: 'Brands' }}"
            style="--at-brands-mobile-cols: {{ mobile_cols }};"
          >
            {%- comment -%}
              Single-pass letter-grouped emission. We track the previous
              letter in `last_letter` and emit a new `.at-panel__letter-section`
              header (closing the prior one if any) whenever the first letter
              changes. This replaces the previous double-nested loop
              (letters × brands × 2) which was the dominant complexity cost
              and the reason this section was 5xx-ing on cold cache.

              theme-check warnings about unbalanced HTML across LiquidBranch
              boundaries are expected and benign — the closing `</div></div>`
              fires on every letter change AND once after the loop, so every
              opener is paired with a closer at runtime.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            {% # theme-check-disable %}
            {%- assign last_letter = '' -%}
            {%- for brand_link in sorted_brands -%}
              {%- liquid
                assign letter = brand_link.title | upcase | slice: 0, 1
                assign brand_icon = blank
                unless icon_source == 'initials_only'
                  assign coll_img = brand_link.object.featured_image
                  if coll_img != blank
                    assign brand_icon = coll_img
                  endif
                endunless
              -%}
              {%- if letter != last_letter -%}
                {%- if last_letter != '' -%}</div></div>{%- endif -%}
                <div
                  class="at-panel__letter-section"
                  id="at-letter-{{ letter }}"
                  role="listitem"
                >
                  <div class="at-panel__letter-header" aria-hidden="true">{{- letter -}}</div>
                  <div class="at-panel__brand-grid">
                {%- assign last_letter = letter -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              <a
                href="{{ brand_link.url }}"
                class="at-panel__brand-item"
                data-brand-name="{{ brand_link.title | escape }}"
                {% if brand_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
              >
                <span
                  class="at-brand-avatar{% if brand_icon != blank %} at-brand-avatar--image{% else %} at-brand-avatar--initials{% endif %}"
                  style="--at-brand-avatar-radius: {{ img_radius }}px;"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  data-brand-name="{{ brand_link.title | escape }}"
                >
                  {%- if brand_icon != blank -%}
                    {{-
                      brand_icon
                      | image_url: width: 48, height: 48, crop: 'center'
                      | image_tag:
                        alt: '',
                        loading: 'lazy',
                        fetchpriority: 'low',
                        decoding: 'async',
                        width: 24,
                        height: 24
                    -}}
                  {%- else -%}
                    {{- brand_link.title | slice: 0, 2 | upcase -}}
                  {%- endif -%}
                </span>
                <span class="at-panel__brand-name">{{- brand_link.title -}}</span>
              </a>
            {%- endfor -%}
            {%- if last_letter != '' -%}</div></div>{%- endif -%}
            {% # theme-check-enable %}
          </div>

          {%- if alpha_letters.size > 0 -%}
            <nav
              ref="alphaBar"
              class="at-panel__alpha-bar"
              aria-label="{{ 'accessibility.skip_to_results_list' | t | default: 'Jump to letter' }}"
            >
              {%- for letter in alpha_letters -%}
                {%- if letter != blank -%}
                  <button
                    type="button"
                    class="at-panel__alpha-btn"
                    data-letter="{{ letter }}"
                    aria-label="{{ letter }}"
                    on:click="/scrollToLetter"
                  >
                    {{- letter -}}
                  </button>
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endfor -%}
            </nav>
          {%- endif -%}
        </div>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%} ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      MOBILE per-category views
      One per category that has children, excluding the brands item.
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- for cat_link in cats_ll.links -%}
      {%- if cat_link.links != blank and cat_link.handle != brands_item -%}
        {%- liquid
          assign has_groups = false
          for sub_link in cat_link.links
            if sub_link.links != blank
              assign has_groups = true
              break
            endif
          endfor

          assign render_images = false
          assign cat_collection_links = cat_link.links | where: 'type', 'collection_link'
          assign cat_catalog_links = cat_link.links | where: 'type', 'catalog_link'
          if cat_collection_links.size > 0 or cat_catalog_links.size > 0
            assign render_images = true
          endif
        -%}
        <div data-at-mount="mobile-view">
          <div class="at-panel__view" data-view="cat-{{ cat_link.handle }}" hidden>

            <div class="at-panel__header">
              <button
                type="button"
                class="at-panel__back"
                aria-label="{{ 'actions.back' | t | default: 'Back' }}"
                on:click="/back"
              >
                <span class="svg-wrapper">{{- 'icon-chevron-left.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}</span>
              </button>
              <h2 class="at-panel__title">{{- cat_link.title | escape -}}</h2>
              <button
                type="button"
                class="at-panel__close"
                aria-label="{{ 'actions.close' | t | default: 'Close menu' }}"
                on:click="header-drawer/close"
              >
                <span class="svg-wrapper">{{- 'icon-close.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}</span>
              </button>
            </div>

            <div class="at-panel__body">
              {%- if has_groups -%}
                {%- for group_link in cat_link.links -%}
                  {%- if group_link.links != blank -%}
                    <div class="at-panel__group">
                      <h3 class="at-panel__group-title">{{- group_link.title -}}</h3>
                      <ul class="at-panel__grid{% if render_images %} at-panel__grid--images{% endif %}" role="list">
                        {%- for item_link in group_link.links -%}
                          <li>
                            <a
                              href="{{ item_link.url }}"
                              class="at-panel__grid-item"
                              {% if item_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
                            >
                              {%- if render_images -%}
                                {%- render 'link-featured-image',
                                  link: item_link,
                                  class: 'at-panel__grid-image',
                                  sizes: 'auto, 200px'
                                -%}
                              {%- endif -%}
                              <span class="at-panel__grid-item-text">{{- item_link.title -}}</span>
                            </a>
                          </li>
                        {%- endfor -%}
                      </ul>
                    </div>
                  {%- else -%}
                    <a
                      href="{{ group_link.url }}"
                      class="at-panel__item at-panel__item--child"
                      {% if group_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
                    >
                      <span class="at-panel__item-text">{{- group_link.title -}}</span>
                    </a>
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endfor -%}

              {%- else -%}
                <ul class="at-panel__grid{% if render_images %} at-panel__grid--images{% endif %}" role="list">
                  {%- for sub_link in cat_link.links -%}
                    <li>
                      <a
                        href="{{ sub_link.url }}"
                        class="at-panel__grid-item"
                        {% if sub_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
                      >
                        {%- if render_images -%}
                          {%- render 'link-featured-image',
                            link: sub_link,
                            class: 'at-panel__grid-image',
                            sizes: 'auto, 200px'
                          -%}
                        {%- endif -%}
                        <span class="at-panel__grid-item-text">{{- sub_link.title -}}</span>
                      </a>
                    </li>
                  {%- endfor -%}
                </ul>
              {%- endif -%}

              {%- if cat_link.url != blank -%}
                <div class="at-panel__view-all">
                  <a href="{{ cat_link.url }}" class="at-panel__view-all-link">
                    Shop all {{ cat_link.title }} →
                  </a>
                </div>
              {%- endif -%}
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}

    {%- comment -%} ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      DESKTOP brand grid (mounts into the live brands cat-content panel)
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- if brand_source_links != blank -%}
      {%- assign brands_grid_id = 'at-brands-grid-desktop' -%}
      <div data-at-mount="desktop-cat-content" data-cat="{{ brands_item }}">
        <div
          class="at-brands-panel__grid-wrapper"
          id="{{ brands_grid_id }}"
          role="list"
          aria-label="{{ brands_cat_link.title | default: 'Brands' }}"
        >
          <div
            class="at-brands-panel__grid"
            style="--at-brands-cols: {{ cols }}; --at-brands-rows: {{ brand_grid_rows }};"
          >
            {%- for brand_link in brand_source_links -%}
              {%- liquid
                assign brand_icon = blank
                unless icon_source == 'initials_only'
                  assign coll_img = brand_link.object.featured_image
                  if coll_img != blank
                    assign brand_icon = coll_img
                  endif
                endunless
              -%}
              <a
                href="{{ brand_link.url }}"
                class="at-brands-panel__brand-item"
                data-brand-name="{{ brand_link.title | escape }}"
                role="listitem"
                {% if brand_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
              >
                <span
                  class="at-brand-avatar{% if brand_icon != blank %} at-brand-avatar--image{% else %} at-brand-avatar--initials{% endif %}"
                  style="--at-brand-avatar-radius: {{ img_radius }}px;"
                  aria-hidden="true"
                  data-brand-name="{{ brand_link.title | escape }}"
                >
                  {%- if brand_icon != blank -%}
                    {{- brand_icon | image_url: width: 48, height: 48, crop: 'center'
                        | image_tag:
                          alt: '',
                          loading: 'lazy',
                          fetchpriority: 'low',
                          decoding: 'async',
                          width: 24,
                          height: 24 -}}
                  {%- else -%}
                    {{- brand_link.title | slice: 0, 2 | upcase -}}
                  {%- endif -%}
                </span>
                <span class="at-brands-panel__brand-name">{{- brand_link.title -}}</span>
              </a>
            {%- endfor -%}
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    {%- endif -%}

    {%- comment -%} ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════
      DESKTOP per-category subnav grids
    ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ {%- endcomment -%}
    {%- for cat_link in cats_ll.links -%}
      {%- if cat_link.handle != brands_item and cat_link.links != blank -%}
        <div data-at-mount="desktop-cat-content" data-cat="{{ cat_link.handle }}">
          <div class="at-brands-panel__grid-wrapper">
            <ul class="at-brands-panel__subnav-grid list-unstyled" role="list">
              {%- for sub_link in cat_link.links -%}
                {%- liquid
                  # Single dereference: previously this was accessed twice
                  # per sub_link (once for the if-blank check, once for the
                  # render), doubling the link.object lookups in this grid.
                  assign sub_img = sub_link.object.featured_image
                -%}
                <li role="listitem">
                  <a
                    href="{{ sub_link.url }}"
                    class="at-brands-panel__subnav-item"
                    {% if sub_link.current %}aria-current="page"{% endif %}
                  >
                    {%- if sub_img != blank -%}
                      <span class="at-brand-avatar at-brand-avatar--image" aria-hidden="true"
                        style="--at-brand-avatar-radius: {{ img_radius }}px;">
                        {{- sub_img
                            | image_url: width: 48, height: 48, crop: 'center'
                            | image_tag:
                              alt: '',
                              loading: 'lazy',
                              fetchpriority: 'low',
                              decoding: 'async',
                              width: 24,
                              height: 24 -}}
                      </span>
                    {%- endif -%}
                    <span class="at-brands-panel__brand-name">{{- sub_link.title -}}</span>
                    {%- if sub_link.links != blank -%}
                      <span class="at-brands-panel__cat-chevron svg-wrapper" aria-hidden="true">
                        {{- 'icon-chevron-right.svg' | inline_asset_content -}}
                      </span>
                    {%- endif -%}
                  </a>
                </li>
              {%- endfor -%}
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}

  </at-menu-data>
{%- endif -%}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "AT Menu Data",
  "tag": "div",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": "Settings here should mirror the AT Menu block (Header → AT Menu). This section emits the heavy menu views that load on demand when a user opens the drawer (mobile) or hovers the nav (desktop). It renders nothing on initial page loads."
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Menu sources"
    },
    {
      "type": "link_list",
      "id": "at_categories_menu",
      "label": "Categories sidebar menu",
      "info": "Match the AT Menu block's 'Categories sidebar menu'."
    },
    {
      "type": "link_list",
      "id": "at_brands_menu",
      "label": "Brands source menu",
      "info": "Match the AT Menu block's 'Brands source menu'."
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "at_brands_item_handle",
      "label": "Brands sidebar item handle",
      "default": "brands"
    },
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Brand grid"
    },
    {
      "type": "select",
      "id": "at_brand_icon_source",
      "label": "Brand icon source",
      "options": [
        { "value": "auto",                  "label": "Auto" },
        { "value": "collection_image_only", "label": "Collection image only" },
        { "value": "initials_only",         "label": "Initials only" }
      ],
      "default": "auto"
    },
    {
      "type": "checkbox",
      "id": "at_show_brand_search",
      "label": "Show brand search",
      "default": true
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "at_brands_panel_columns",
      "label": "Desktop columns",
      "min": 3, "max": 6, "step": 1, "default": 4
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "at_brands_mobile_columns",
      "label": "Mobile columns",
      "min": 1, "max": 3, "step": 1, "default": 2
    },
    {
      "type": "range",
      "id": "at_brand_image_border_radius",
      "label": "Brand image border radius",
      "min": 0, "max": 32, "step": 1, "unit": "px", "default": 4
    }
  ]
}
{% endschema %}
